<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Etherix Server FAQ</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #1e1e1e;
            color: #f0f0f0;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #272727;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 2em;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        main {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #2c2c2c;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
        }
        h2 {
            color: #ffd700;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
        p, ul {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding-left: 0;
        }
        ul li::before {
            content: "» ";
            color: #00ff00;
        }
        code {
            background-color: #444;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            color: #ffd700;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>Etherix Server FAQ</header>
    <main>
        <h2>How to claim land?</h2>
        <p>To claim land, you need a <strong>Golden Shovel</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right-click one corner of the area you want to claim.</li>
            <li>Right-click the opposite corner.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The land between these two points will now be claimed.</p>
        <p>To allow someone to build or interact on your claim, use:</p>
        <p><code>/trust &lt;playername&gt;</code> – This lets that player build and interact on your claimed land.</p>
        <p>To remove all your claims, use: <code>/abandonallclaims</code></p>

        <h2>How to claim daily rewards?</h2>
        <p>You can claim your daily rewards once every 24 hours using:</p>
        <p><code>/daily</code></p>
        <p>When you claim your reward, you will receive a <strong>Daily Crate Key</strong>. You can use this key at the <strong>Crates area</strong> located at <strong>Survival Spawn</strong>.</p>

        <h2>I have VIP. What benefits do I get?</h2>
        <p>With the <strong>VIP rank</strong>, you receive the following benefits:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>/back</code> – Return to your previous location</li>
            <li><code>/enderchest</code> – Open your Ender Chest anywhere</li>
            <li><code>/hat</code> – Put any item on your head</li>
            <li><code>/near</code> – See players near you</li>
            <li><code>/workbench</code> – Open a crafting table anywhere</li>
            <li><strong>[VIP]</strong> – Special rank in chat</li>
            <li>VIP Crate Key – Receive 1 VIP crate key every 24 hours using <code>/viprewards</code></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How do I get money on the server?</h2>
        <p>Earn <strong>passive money</strong> by doing activities like enchanting, woodcutting, mining, and more.</p>
        <p>Check all available jobs and the leaderboard using:</p>
        <p><code>/jobs</code></p>
        <p>You can also sell items to earn money:</p>
        <p><code>/sell hand</code> – Sells the item you are currently holding.</p>

        <h2>How do I join events?</h2>
        <p>Events are announced in-game or on Discord. Keep an eye on announcements and join at the scheduled time to win prizes!</p>

        <h2>How do I teleport to friends?</h2>
        <p>Use <code>/tpa &lt;player&gt;</code> to send a teleport request. The other player must accept it using <code>/tpaccept</code> for the teleport to happen.</p>

        <h2>How do I open crates?</h2>
        <p>Use a crate key that matches the crate type (for example, a <strong>Food Key</strong> opens a <strong>Food Crate</strong>).</p>
        <p>You can use your key at the <strong>Crates area</strong>, located at <strong>Survival Spawn</strong>.</p>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
